      <description>&lt;p&gt;The way I remember it is hash &lt;code&gt;#&lt;/code&gt; and bang &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; â€“ hashbang &lt;code&gt;#!&lt;/code&gt; which sounds like &lt;code&gt;shebang&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s a good idea to include a shebang &lt;code&gt;#!&lt;/code&gt; at the top of a Bash file. This is so that the sript runs correctly regardless of what shell the user is running.&lt;/p&gt;
